# T04 – Docker Default Parameters

This folder covers Docker default parameters, package verification, daemon info, and user permissions.

---

<details>
<summary>1. Verify Docker Package Installation</summary>

Check if `docker-ce` and `docker-cli` are installed in the VM.

```bash
dpkg -l | grep docker-ce
Explanation:

dpkg -l → Lists all installed packages

grep docker-ce → Filters output to show Docker-related packages

</details> <details> <summary>2. Verify Docker Compose Plugin Installation</summary>
dpkg -l | grep docker-compose-plugin

</details> <details> <summary>3. Verify Docker Version</summary>
docker --version

</details> <details> <summary>4. Detailed Docker Info</summary>
docker info


Key Information Displayed:

Docker client & server info

Container status & images

Cgroup driver & version

Plugins (volumes, network)

Docker Swarm status

Default runtime

Docker host OS kernel

Docker root directory

</details> <details> <summary>5. Docker Root Directory</summary>

Default Docker root directory: /var/lib/docker

To list files:

ls -l /var/lib/docker/

</details> <details> <summary>6. Default Docker Registry</summary>

Registry URL: https://index.docker.io/v1/

Docker images from this path are downloaded locally by Docker CLI to create containers.

</details> <details> <summary>7. Normal User Permissions</summary>

By default, non-root users have restrictions.

Running docker info as a normal user shows client info only, not server details.

</details> <details> <summary>8. Allow Normal User to Run Docker Commands</summary>

Step 1: Check Docker Group

cat /etc/group | grep docker
cat /etc/passwd | grep docker


Step 2: Add User to Docker Group

sudo usermod -aG docker testuser
cat /etc/group | grep docker


Step 3: Restart Docker Service

sudo systemctl restart docker
sudo systemctl status docker


Docker service should be active (running).

Step 4: Test as Normal User

su - testuser
docker info


If commands still fail, reboot the VM:

sudo reboot


After relogin, docker info should work.

Note: Docker CLI connects to the server via /var/run/docker.sock.

